+**Fixture-ownership decision (decided, not deferred).** The base `iut` fixture
+([`plugin.py`](../../conformance/src/conformance/harness/plugin.py) ~L216) keeps
+its `adapter` instance *local* and yields only an `IutHandle` ‚Äî downstream
+fixtures never see the adapter object, so they cannot call `crash_restart()` on
+it. Rather than widen the shared base fixtures (which every scenario depends on),
+the durability fixture **owns its own adapter lifecycle**, patterned exactly on
+the existing [`receiver_iut`](../../conformance/scenarios/conftest.py) fixture:
+it instantiates `iut_adapter_factory()` itself, calls `start(...)`, seeds its own
+default workers, holds the adapter reference so it can call `crash_restart()`,
+and tears the adapter down in its own `finally`. This keeps the change **off** the
+shared `iut` / `wire_client` / `default_workers` path entirely ‚Äî `plugin.py` is
+NOT touched. (The rejected alternative ‚Äî exposing the adapter through the base
+`iut` fixture ‚Äî would touch a session-critical fixture used by all ~56 scenarios
+for no benefit the self-owned fixture doesn't already give.)
