+**Companion control-plane subprocess on restart.** `ReferenceAdapter.start()`
+also spawns a `ControlPlaneSubprocess` and returns its URL on the handle. A naive
+`crash_restart` that just re-runs the whole `start()` path would either leak a
+second control-plane process or rotate `control_plane_base_url` needlessly. The
+durability scenarios do not exercise chapter 11, so `crash_restart` **restarts
+only the task-store-server** (SIGKILL + re-spawn against the same store file) and
+**preserves the existing control-plane subprocess + its URL** on the fresh handle.
+The re-spawn path is therefore a *factored subset* of `start()` (the
+task-store-server spawn + port-read + stderr-drain), not a full `start()` re-call
+‚Äî refactor `start()` so that subset is a private helper both paths share.
